Race.SummaryText:
PROPOSITION
(CREATING A FORTY-SECOND JUDICIAL DISTRICT COURT)
Race.FullText:
FOR the proposition that the Eleventh Judicial District be divided, effective January 1, 2009, by the establishment of the Forty-Second Judicial District composed of DeSoto Parish, and continuing the Eleventh Judicial District composed of Sabine Parish as provided by Act No. 416 of the 2007 Regular Session of the Legislature of Louisiana. 

AGAINST the proposition that the Eleventh Judicial District be divided, effective January 1, 2009, by the establishment of the Forty-Second Judicial District composed of DeSoto Parish, and continuing the Eleventh Judicial District composed of Sabine Parish as provided by Act No. 416 of the 2007 Regular Session of the Legislature of Louisiana.

Race.SpecificTitle: Acad-Evng Fire Prot. Dist -- $750,000 Bond - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
FIRE PROTECTION DISTRICT PROPOSITION
 (BONDS)

SUMMARY:  AUTHORITY TO ISSUE $750,000 OF 10-YEAR GENERAL OBLIGATION BONDS OF ACADIA-EVANGELINE FIRE PROTECTION DISTRICT FOR ACQUIRING, CONSTRUCTING AND IMPROVING BUILDINGS, MACHINERY AND EQUIPMENT, INCLUDING BOTH REAL AND PERSONAL PROPERTY, TO BE USED IN GIVING FIRE PROTECTION TO THE PROPERTY IN SAID DISTRICT, SAID BONDS TO BE PAYABLE FROM AD VALOREM TAXES.
Race.FullText: Shall Acadia-Evangeline Fire Protection District of the Parishes of Acadia and Evangeline, State of Louisiana (the "District"), incur debt and issue bonds to the amount of Seven Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($750,000) to run ten (10) years from the date thereof, with interest at a rate or rates not exceeding seven per centum (7%) per annum, for the purpose of acquiring, constructing and improving buildings, machinery and equipment, including both real and personal property, title to which shall be in the public, to be used in giving fire protection to the property in the District, which bonds will be general obligations of the District and will be payable from ad valorem taxes to be levied and collected in the manner provided by Article VI, Section 33 of the Constitution of the State of Louisiana of 1974, and statutory authority supplemental thereto?

Race.SpecificTitle: Fire Prot. Dist. No. 6 -- 16 Mills - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
FIRE PROTECTION DISTRICT NO. 6 PROPOSITION
(MILLAGE)

SUMMARY:  10-YEAR 16-MILLS PROPERTY TAX FOR ACQUIRING, CONSTRUCTING, MAINTAINING AND OPERATING THE DISTRICT'S FIRE PROTECTION AND EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICE FACILITIES, FOR PURCHASING FIRE TRUCKS AND OTHER FIRE FIGHTING OR EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICE EQUIPMENT AND PAYING THE COST OF OBTAINING WATER FOR FIRE PROTECTION PURPOSES INCLUDING CHARGES FOR FIRE HYDRANT RENTALS AND SERVICE.
Race.FullText: Shall Fire Protection District No. 6 of the Parish of Terrebonne and the Parish of Lafourche, State of Louisiana (the "District"), levy a sixteen (16) mills tax on all property subject to taxation in said District (an estimated $465,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year) for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2008 and ending with the year 2017, for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, maintaining and operating the District's fire protection and emergency medical service facilities, for purchasing fire trucks and other fire fighting or emergency medical service equipment and paying the cost of obtaining water for fire protection purposes including charges for fire hydrant rentals and service?

Race.SpecificTitle: Parishwide -- 4 Mills - Florida Juv. Justice Commission
Race.SummaryText:
PARISHWIDE PROPOSITION
(FLORIDA PARISHES JUVENILE JUSTICE DISTRICT)

SUMMARY:  10 YEAR, 4 MILLS PROPERTY TAX FOR ACQUIRING, CONSTRUCTING, IMPROVING, MAINTAINING AND OPERATING JUVENILE DETENTION FACILITIES FOR THE FLORIDA PARISHES JUVENILE JUSTICE DISTRICT AND ACQUIRING, MAINTAINING AND OPERATING NECESSARY EQUIPMENT AND FURNISHING FOR SUCH FACILITIES, SAID TAX TO BE SUBJECT TO HOMESTEAD EXEMPTION AS PROVIDED BY LAW.
Race.FullText: Shall the Florida Parishes Juvenile Justice District (the "District") levy a special tax of four (4) mills on all property subject to taxation in the District for a period of ten (10) years, beginning with the year 2008 and ending with the year 2017 (an estimated $7,200,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for the purpose of acquiring, constructing, improving, maintaining and operating juvenile detention facilities for the District and acquiring, maintaining and operating necessary equipment and furnishings for such facilities, said tax to be subject to homestead exemption as provided by law?
